        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 1:55PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 155 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Beverly, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marietta, Belpre, Beverly, Chesterhill, Lowell, Stockport, Macksburg,
Lower Salem, Fleming, Hackney, Bartlett, and Devola.

This includes Interstate 77 in Ohio between mile markers 4 and 17.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
